  "prompt": "Which is correct, \"queue the music\" or \"cue the music,\" and why?",
  "response": "\"Cue the music\" is the correct phrase. Here's why:\n\n\u2022 \"Cue\" means to give a signal for something to start or to provide a prompt.\n\u2022 In theatrical, film, or musical contexts, a \"cue\" is a signal to begin an action or performance.\n\u2022 \"Queue\" means a line or sequence of people or things waiting to be processed, which is not related to signaling something to start.\n\nSo when you want to signal the start of music, the correct phrase is \"cue the music.\"",
